# Habitat Website Rebuild Walkthrough

## What Was Accomplished
I successfully rebuilt the `joinhabitat.eu` website following the aesthetic cues of modern startup hubs like Solo Founders, YCombinator, and The Bridge. The new website uses a Next.js 14 App Router foundation, styled with Tailwind CSS, and is enhanced with interactive Framer Motion animations. 

The site features a dark, premium theme enhanced by subtle mesh gradients and glassmorphism UI elements that create a dynamic, highly polished feel.

### Key Components Built
- **[Navigation.tsx]**: A sticky, blur-backed header that animates smoothly upon scroll.
- **[Hero.tsx]**: A powerful entry section featuring glowing backgrounds, a dynamic statistics tag, textured gradient text ("The fastest way to launch your startup"), magnetic primary buttons, and subdued logos of top VCs.
- **[ValueProps.tsx]**: A glassmorphic bento-box grid detailing the core tenets ("A Residency for Builders," "Ship tonight," "Real feedback," "Momentum").
- **[Testimonials.tsx]**: A section showcasing real quotes from past founders, underlined by high-contrast statistics (e.g., 200+ Participants).
- **[Perks.tsx]**: A sleek group of cards highlighting benefits like mentorship and Lovable credits.
- **[FAQ.tsx]**: An elegantly animated, smooth-expanding accordion for common questions.
- **[Footer.tsx]**: A clean, minimal footer grouping community and connection links.

## Validation Results
I ran the Next.js development server locally and used my browser integration to interact with the site. The rendering matches our design goals precisely.

